content:
Change the Data Category Path Shown in Your Site

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions with the Customer Service Catalog add-on license.

To build and configure Service Catalog site pages and components, you need Permissions and licenses associated with the LWR Service Catalog Site Builder.

The parent category is set to Help by default. So, from the example, the category path is Help > Account Services > Billing. To change the Help category name, use Salesforce Workbench.

From Salesforce Workbench, on the QUERIES tab, enter this query and copy the listed Id and NetworkID of the rows from the blank DataCategoryName and DataCategoryGroupName columns.

SELECT Id, NetworkId, Network.name, DataCategoryName, DataCategoryGroupName, Label, Description FROM NetworkDataCategory WHERE Network.Name='LWR Service Catalog Site'

From the UTILITIES tab, under REST EXPLORER, select PATCH. Make these edits to the query:

Replace ${communityId} with your copied ID.
Replace ${networkDataCategoryId} with your copied NetworkID
Affix ?label={} to the end of the query where {} contains the new parent category name.

/services/data/v61.0/connect/communities/0DBOG0000001bo84AA/network-data-category/0DBOG0000001bo84AA?label=Products and Services

Confirm your updates in your published and activated Service Catalog site. Proceed to Launching Your Service Catalog Site.
title: Changing Data Category Path in Service Cloud
